      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "You should argue that these policies were designed for the perceived stability and order of the time. Proponents at the time viewed zoning as a necessary tool to maintain property values and prevent the perceived decline of desirable neighborhoods. Furthermore, redlining was often justified by the belief that it channeled investment into areas deemed \"safe\" and financially sound for lending institutions. These arguments centered on a very specific, often flawed, economic model of risk management and neighborhood preservation.",
